── 1. MEDICAL MODEL CHECKPOINTS & BINARIES ──
Heavy weights, zip files, and model directories must never be pushed to GitHub
spineai-backend/models/best_efficientnet_s4/
spineai-backend/models/best_efficientnet_se_s4/
*.pth
*.onnx
*.zip
*.tar.gz
*.mar

── 2. LOCAL VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENTS ──
Exclude your local python environment completely from source control
venv/
/venv/
.venv/
env/
ENV/
bin/
lib/
lib64/
include/
share/
pyvenv.cfg

── 3. PYTHON INTERMEDIATE RUNTIME TRASH & CACHE ──
Prevents bytecode caching files from polluting repo commits
pycache/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
spineai-backend/app/pycache/
.pytest_cache/
.exec/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

── 4. CONFIGURATIONS & ENVIRONMENT SECRETS ──
Never commit database passwords, API endpoints, or environment definitions
.env
.env.*
spineai-backend/.env
spineai-frontend/.env

── 5. CONTAINER ARCHITECTURE VOLUMES ──
Ignore local runtime tracking and mapped docker volumes
.docker/
docker-data/
postgres-data/
*.log

── 6. IDE, EDITORS, & SYSTEM JUNK ──
Clean up editor metadata structures and thumbnail index tracks
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
.ntvs
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.swp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini